    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-16T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-16T15:00:00-05:00" n="214"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/661</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-16T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 16, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>408. Your 991, November 15, 9 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d214fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> Try advise <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">Francis</persName>
                    Department has nothing from him since his 1964, November 8. Apparently wireless
                    stations also blocked. Please continue to advise Department which is anxious for
                    information conditions specially welfare Embassy and Consulate staffs and other
                    Americans in Russia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
